    {
      "id": "attendance_policy",
      "title": "Attendance Policy",
      "elements": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "style": "body",
          "content": "Instructors take roll at the beginning of each class lecture and clinic. Students arriving more than five (5) minutes late are considered tardy. After a student accumulates three (3) tardy warnings, they will receive one (1) absence."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "style": "body",
          "content": "It is highly recommended that students attend all classes due to the concentrated learning structure of the course. Except for family emergencies and serious illness, students should plan on attending all classes. After three missed classes, the student will be terminated from the program. Refunds do not apply when a student is dropped by the school for attendance."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "style": "body",
          "content": "Students are required to complete 40 hours of internship/externship in a dental office of their choice. Internship/externship hours are mandatory."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "refund_policy",
      "title": "Refund and Cancellation Policy",
      "elements": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "style": "body",
          "content": "Students have 72 hours from the date of the enrollment agreement to cancel or rescind the agreement and receive a refund of the total tuition and fees (not including uniform cost) paid toward tuition at the time of execution."
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "ordered": true,
          "items": [
            "Students wishing to withdraw must send an email to c.oliver@atldentalassistant.com requesting a withdrawal form.",
            "Students must sign and complete a withdrawal form and submit it to the campus president.",
            "Students shall return any items or equipment to the school.",
            "The withdrawal form date will be used as the last date of enrollment to calculate any refunds."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "style": "body",
          "content": "Students requesting to withdraw for illness or personal reasons may resume their course of study in the next class series. Refunds are granted at a prorated percentage based on the amount of the program completed, up to 50%. Refunds are processed within 45 days of withdrawal. No refunds are issued after 50% of the program is completed."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "style": "body",
          "content": "Students financed by external partners will follow the refund and cancellation policies outlined by their financing company."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "career_services",
      "title": "Career Services",
      "elements": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "style": "body",
          "content": "Atlanta Academy of Dental Assisting will direct and manage career services to assist all students and alumni with the search for a position as a dental assistant. Students perform mock interviews, prepare resumes and cover letters, and receive job-search preparation."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "style": "body",
          "content": "The academy cannot guarantee employment or a specific salary range upon graduation, but will provide placement assistance."
        }
      ]
    },
